To add a bit, the motivation is providing a type-safe wrapper around `Ember.get(someObj, 'a.b')`. We want to be able to do a `safeGet(someObj, 'a', 'b')` which simply dispatches internally to the relevant path, but which does type-checking on the supplied keys ‚Äì for an API that's *slightly* less ergonomic than the built-in Ember API, but which is much nicer than doing it the way we are presently.

```ts
// current way to do it to get type inference
const a = get(someObj, 'a');
const b = get(a, 'b');

// desired API
const b = safeGet(someObj, 'a', 'b');
```

