Well, you have `U extends keyof T = keyof T`, so for `T = IUserModel` `U = 'id' | 'age'` hence `T[U] = string | number`.

A possible fix is:
```ts
let userModel: Model<IUserModel, 'age'> = new Model({id: 'user', age: 0});
let age = userModel.value( 'age' ); // age: number
```

However, I think you are looking for:
```ts
class Model<T> {
    constructor( private entity: T ) {}

    public value<U extends keyof T>( key: U ): T[ U ] {
        return this.entity[ key ];
    }
}

interface IUserModel {
    id: string;
    age: number;
}

let userModel: Model<IUserModel> = new Model({id: 'user', age: 0});
let age = userModel.value( 'age' ); // number
let id = userModel.value( 'id' ); // string
```

