comments.body:
This is just the behaviour of JavaScript.  When using `class` in a ES6 compatible environment, you get an error when you called an improperly bound method:

``` javascript
class A {
    constructor() {
        this.count = 10;
    }
    AddOne() {
        this.count += 1;
    }
}

const a = new A();
const myaddone = a.AddOne;

myaddone();  // Uncaught TypeError: Cannot read property 'count' of undefined
```

Therefore if your suggestion would break compatibility with ES6 classes.

If you need a reference of a method bound to an instance, just bind it:

``` typescript
const myaddone = a.AddOne.bind(a);
```

