comments.body:
It's generally never safe to have circular module dependencies that require immediate execution. You need to re-order your file:

``` ts
abstract class A {
    static create(param: string) {
        switch (param) {
            case "B":
                return new B();
            case "C":
                return new C();
            default:
                break;
        }
    }

    abstract show(): void;
}

export default A;

import B from "./B";
import C from "./C";
```

The problem is that when `B` and `C` are loaded from the `import` in `A`, they execute _before_ the `A` class has been created or exported.

