> A module that uses `export =` to export a non-module entity in place of the module itself must be imported using the existing `import x = require("foo")` syntax as is the case today.

So, one way is to modify A.ts:

``` ts
import X = require("Y");
```

Another way, as the error msg suggest, modify Y.ts:

``` ts
var Y = { a: 1 };
export { Y as default };
```

Unless you're interfacing with existing CommonJS or AMD modules, I would avoid the `export =` construct. Instead, use the new module constructs introduced in ES6:

``` typescript
// ------ y.ys ------
export default { a: 1 };

// ------ a.ts ------
