I've taken a crack at this for my contribution to TypeScript.

When creating the completion entries in competions.ts `createCompletionEntry` all entries are given a `sortText` of `"0"` which means they end up in the default alphabetical order. My logic is to give the symbols merged from `Function` sortText that will cause them to appear after. The concept that seems to indicate these symbols are from an inherited class are the `mergeId` so I have gone for something similar to the following:

```
let sortText = '0';

if(symbol.parent.mergeId) { // undefined on symbols directly from 'C' but numerical for Function symbols
    sortText = `0-${symbol.parent.mergeId}`;
}
```

If this doesn't sound too far off then I would happily follow the standard procedure and create a pull request etc.

