comments.body:
We made a similar change with shorthand properties in #1184 and it is a desirable change. The idea is that in this example, if you are already on that definition you are clearly disinterested in where the variable definition is coming from, so we allow you to jump to the property definition.

This way, you can always get back to the property from a variable declaration with an extra `F12` or whatever your editor's Go-To-Definition supports.

For example:

``` TypeScript
interface I {
    /*afterTwoGoToDefs*/property: string;
}

let x: I;
let { /*afterOneGoToDef*/property } = x;

/*goToDefOnHere*/property += " hello";
```

